Sure it can.  That's the whole big humongous overwhelming problem with both Muslims and non-Muslims on this issue.  There are very very few elements in the Qur'an that are absolute.. what we need these days is a reinterpretation, and it's not just little ol' me posting here who thinks so, but many many of the best and brightest of our scholars (most of whom can't live anywhere in the Middle East or risk being arrested)... I mean, if you take an honest look at early Islamic history, there were no absolutes.. the law was shifted to accommodate the circumstances.  For example, during the time of the Caliph Umar, one of the most highly regarded personages in Islam, he frequently abandoned implementation of certain Islamic rules when the situation warranted it... he also placed women in high places of power, like heading up the central marketplace, etc.  Try something like that now in many Muslims countries and it's &quot;Off with your head!&quot; -- literally.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying Islamic goverment is a substitute for a secular one.  Obviously, if you're not Muslim you will have some issues, but it should be a decent place to live, where non-Muslims may very well choose to live because life is good there, regardless of what the overriding theology is.  Unfortunately the only non-Muslims I know of who want to live in Muslim-majority countries these days are people who want to a) make a lot of money and/or b) convert the populace to another faith.  The countries have not made it pleasant enough to want to live there simply for the sake of the overall society (although I hear some countries are making progress -- like Qatar, Bahrain...)<br>
<br>
Kate <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=138.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=138.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=138.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=38><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=138.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.threadControl?topicID=138.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=138.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=138.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action